.TH "serdev_controller_alloc" 9 "serdev_controller_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
serdev_controller_alloc \- Allocate a new serdev controller
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct serdev_controller *" serdev_controller_alloc
.BI "(struct device *parent "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "parent" 12
parent device
.IP "size" 12
size of private data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Caller is responsible for either calling \fBserdev_controller_add\fP to add the
newly allocated controller, or calling \fBserdev_controller_put\fP to discard it.
The allocated private data region may be accessed via
\fBserdev_controller_get_drvdata\fP
